  "texts": [
    "Since graph data often contains a large number of nodes and edges, performing graph pooling operations can face the challenge of high computational complexity.",
    "As the scale of graph data increases, the computation time may grow exponentially, which makes it difficult for graph pooling methods to achieve immediate response in practical applications.",
    "For example, in real-time traffic analysis or online social network analysis, it is critical to process large-scale graph data quickly and accurately.",
    "In addition, the unstructured nature of graph data makes it difficult to fully utilize traditional parallel computing resources by graph pooling methods, which further exacerbates the problem of computational efficiency.",
    "Even with powerful computational resources, if graph data cannot be processed in parallel, the computation time cannot be significantly reduced."
  ],
